///   or you risk orphaned work and unobserved exceptions.
///
/// - OperationCanceledException is expected during shutdown — catch it at
///   the loop boundary, not deeper in business logic.
///
/// - If ProcessItem does database work, pass the same CancellationToken to
///   your DbCommand/transaction so it cancels cooperatively rather than
///   leaving connections hanging.
